# ADR-001: Multi-Tenant Strategy

## Status

Accepted

## Date

2026-06-28

## Context

Famm is the first application built on top of a broader relationship-commerce platform. The platform must eventually support multiple businesses, professionals, communities, customers, applications, and industries.

If tenant ownership is not designed into the data model from the beginning, the platform may become difficult to scale, secure, or adapt for future organizations and applications.

The platform must support:

- Independent providers
- Multi-provider businesses
- Communities
- Future vertical applications
- Third-party applications
- Multiple industries
- Separate customer networks
- Role-based access control
- Future API consumers and AI agents

## Decision

All tenant-sensitive business records must include a tenant ownership field.

The platform will use `organization_id` as the primary tenant boundary for business-owned records.

Where a record may not belong to an organization, the platform may use `tenant_id` or `owner_user_id`, but that exception must be documented.

The default ownership pattern is:

```text
organization_id
created_at
updated_at
created_by
deleted_at, when soft deletion is required
```

All application logic must enforce tenant scoping when reading, writing, updating, or deleting tenant-sensitive records.

## Layer

Platform Core

## Platform Primitives Affected

- User
- Organization
- Community
- Relationship
